Background Information
----------------------

	There is no automated install process available for The Cog
Development Application (or "CogDevApp"), so a manual install is
necessary. There are two sets of programs that come with the CogDevApp,
one written in Python/GTK, which is used for the GUI design of game
modules for the Cog Engine, and a second set which is written in Jython,
used for the conversion between the Python/GTK files used by the
CogDevApp, and the Java files used by the Cog Engine to play the games.

	A future version of the CogEngine itself will be rewritten such
that Jython will no longer be necessary for converting between programs.

	The Java-based "Text2Cog" program is now depricated, and will not
be maintained in the future.

	Since complete documentation is not currently available for the
CogDevApp, it may be useful to refer to the Cycon Odyssey, the demo game
for the CogEngine. The Cycon Odyssey is also in an unfinished state, but
there is more than enough there to reach an understanding of how to use
the Cog Developement Application. The Cycon Odyssey is available at the
CogEngine homepage, link listed below.


Prerequisits
------------

Python/GTK information is available at:
http://www.daa.com.au/~james/pygtk/
http://theopenlab.uml.edu/pygtools/

Jython information is available at:
http://jython.sourceforge.net/

(You also need the Python/Gnome Libraries, and the Glade Libraries)

Python/Gnome information is available at:
http://www.daa.com.au/~james/gnome/

Glade information is available at:
http://glade.gnome.org/


If you are using RedHat Linux, the following rpms (and their own
prerequisits) should be installed:
python
pygtk
pygnome
pygtk-libglade
pygnome-libglade

	All of these packages are included on the RedHat install cds,
as of version 7.1. If I have missed any packages, please email me.

If you are using Debian Linux, the following debs (and their own
prerequisits) should be installed:
python-base
python-gtk
python-gnome
python-glade
libglade
libglade-gnome

	Again, all of these packages are available as part of the base
install, as of version 2.2 (potato).


Quick Installation Instructions
-------------------------------

1) Download and install the above listed prerequisits.

2) Uncompress and extract the source files.

3) Edit the import_cog_data.py and export_cog_data.py scripts such that
the "cPython_library_path" variable points to your local installation of
python.

4) You can execute the CogDevApp GUI program by typing ./CogDevApp.py in
the resulting directory.

5) You can convert game modules create with the CogDevApp into files
readable by the Cog Engine via the "export_cog_data.py" script, and you
convert those file back for editing using the "import_cog_data.py" script.

6) The current version of the CogDevApp includes class files from version
0.91 of the CogEngine (the current version). If you are going to be using
CogDevApp with a different version of the CogEngine, you will need to
replace these class files with the new ones.


Example (Under Linux):
tar xvzf CogDevApp-0.82-source.tar.gz
tar xvzf CyconOdyssey-0.91-data.tar.gz
cp CyconOdyssey-0.91/Cycon-COG.dat CogDevApp-0.82
cd CogDevApp-0.82
./import_cog_data.py Cycon-COG.dat Cycon-COG.dev
./CogDevApp.py Cycon-COG.dev
./export_cog_data.py Cycon-COG.dev Cycon-COG.dat


